OL,3,CGraduates accuse government of acting
OL,4,Clike 'loan sharks' over student debt
OL,6,FDuring a phone-in on LBC on whether
OL,7,Fshe agreed with the Chancellor, Ms
OL,8,FPowell said: "Well, look, as a parent
OL,9,Fmyself with a son who is also in the
OL,10,FPlan 2 scheme, I've been following
OL,11,Fthese issues very closely, actually,
OL,12,Ffor a number of years... I (don't)
OL,13,Fjust hear you, I feel you as well,
OL,14,Fbecause I think the idea of having a
OL,15,Floan ` and really it isn't a loan,
OL,16,Fit's a kind of graduate tax ` but
OL,17,Fhaving a loan that you are paying off
OL,18,Fin work, but you're not actually
OL,19,Fmaking any progress in paying it off,
OL,20,Fand that feels endless, and these high
OL,21,Finterest rates, you know, does feel
OL,22,Funfair.
